No fewer than 59 girls between the ages of 13 and 15 were arrested early Saturday morning arrested at two hotels in parts of Calabar metropolis where they engage in prostitution. The Cross River State Director, Department of State Security (DSS), Deacon Adebayo Ilupeju, who briefed journalists on the arrests in Calabar, said the girls have been profiled and the Zonal office of National Agency for the Prohibition of Trafficking in Persons, (NAPTIP) in Uyo, Akwa Ibom State, contacted for necessary evacuation. Ilupeju said most of the girls who volunteered information, said some women “conscripted” them into prostitution and are making weekly returns to them.  Nigerian secret Police burst sex cartel in Calabar, arrest 59 girls, men 7 suspects nabbed for smuggling, human trafficking Our worker not a kidnapper — DSS Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin